t to do, amazing landscapes and is a mix of different cultures, so they are very friendly with the foreigners. The food is really good, especially their special pizza, the deep dish pizza.    Aline Pantano and Maria Gehlen | Brazil       Chicago Attractions       Go to slide 1    Go to slide 2    Go to slide 3    Go to slide 4                Go to the next slide    Go to the previous slide       Buckingham Fountain              Go to the next slide    Go to the previous slide       Navy Pier              Go to the next slide    Go to the previous slide       Field Museum              Go to the next slide    Go to the previous slide       Chicago Bean            Public Transportation in Chicago      Chicago and the UIC campus are both easy to navigate and excellent for walking, biking and taking public transportation.  The Chicago train and bus system is called Chicago Transit Authority (CTA). The CTA is the second largest public transportation system in the U.S., with rail and bus lines within the City of Chicago and 40 neighboring communities.  UIC has its own convenient stop along the CTA Blue Line train: UIC-Halsted      Weather in Chicago         Chicago is known as the ‘Windy City’ partly because it is located on Lake Michigan, which creates a strong lake breeze.         You can experience all four seasons while in Chicago        Months  Weather  What students wear      Winter  December, January, February  Cold  Heavy Coat, Boots, Scarves, Gloves, Hats    Spring  March, April, May  Warm, Rainy  Raincoat, Boots, Sweaters    Summer  June, July, August  Hot, Sunny  Sandals, Shorts, Sunglasses    Fall  September, October, November  Chilly, Cool  Light Jacket, Sweater, Boots, Scarves              Request More Information   Contact us to learn more about the English programs at the Tutorium.    Request Info            Student Life    Back to main content           Experience UIC    Studying in Chicago    Housing and Dining                  UIC Logo        The Tutoriu